main event: An observer saw an oblong, greenish-blue object in the sky moving up and down and in a slight circle for 21 minutes in Twig, Minnesota.
interesting points: The object was described as star-like and emitted color,It was observed at a 70-degree azimuth and 10-degree elevation,The sighting was conducted using binoculars,The object appeared at around 7 degrees above the horizon,The object's movement was stationary and then up and down.
